message: [[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'The Bhatias are a class of Rajputs, originally coming from Bhatner, Jaisalmer and the Rajputana desert.   Ibetson D.C.J., Reports on the Census of the Punjab taken on 17th February, 1881, Vol.I, p. 297; Crooke W.(ed) The Tribes and Castes of the North-Western Provinces and Oudh, Vol. II, pp. 37-38 ; Dr. Mangala B. Purandare, "History of The Bhatia Community ", Volume I, pp. 4, Published by Global Bhatia Foundation, January, 2012.'
/* History */Added content based on reliable references
/* Bhatia rajputs, chadravanshi clan */ new section

According to Late Sir Denzil Ibbetson who gathered much information on martial castes of punjab, Bhatias are a class of rajputs, originally coming from Bhatner, Jaiselmer and the Rajputana desert, who have taken to commercial pursuits. . <ref>Ibbetson, panjab castes, Reports on the Census of the Punjab taken on 17th February, 1881, Vol.I, p. 297.</ref>
